#UTF-8 MAgicRK(1) . .
//`RFG27`„ÅÆAlice Dosconio: Make Mika a General-Purpose-Programming-or-Marking-Language.
//`RFB14`„ÅÆAlice Dosconio: Mika is from `Micro Core` or `Mecocoa Integrated Compilation Assembly`. Henceforth, Mika is the compilers collection of the Mana. `Ma` is from `Make`, na is from `Arina/Phina` and `Haruno(Haruna)`. The name may be ‚ÄúMano‚Äù in the future.
//`RFC29`„ÅÆAlice Dosconio: Make Mika into a ML.
//`RFX03`„ÅÆAlice Dosconio: `Mediation and General-purpose Language Compolation` (Mgl), .ML is the pre-processed documentof .Mgl.
//`RFX23`„ÅÆAlice Dosconio: Rename into `Magicoll`(Universal Logical Linear Language) from `Mika` and bought the domain `magicoll.org`. 
//`20240202`„ÅÆAlice Dosconio: Bought the domain `magice.org`.

Inline("tex", "\\labex{Magice}\n");

Title(3, "Introduction");
Format("^Balias^b: ^TUniversal Logical Linear Language^t;\n");
Format("^Bdomain^b: ");
Inline("tex", "\\href{http://magice.org}{magice.org};\n");
Format("^Bassembly source extension^b: `.a';\n");
Format("^BMagice source extension^b: `.m', `.mg', `.src'; (some format conflict with this: MATLAB, Objective-C)\n");
Format("^Bheader extension^b: `.h', `.mgh';\n");
Format("^Bused-name^b magicoll, mika(now a middle language).\n");

Title(3, "Component");
Format("^Bcompiler^b: `mgc', `magic';\n");
Format("Special:\n");
Format("1. The name of registers and instructions can be identifiers if defined ^M_KWRD_ASM^m or in block `unsafe'.\n");

Title(3, "Optimizer");
Format("Magice have 3 built-in optimizing modes:\n");
ListBegin("itemize");
	ListItem("", "^Mmgc -O^m + level: for running efficiency;");
	ListItem("", "^Mmgc -Om^m + level: for memory occupation;");
	ListItem("", "^Mmgc -Oo^m + level: for binary output occupation.");
ListEnd();

Title(3, "for non-binary system architectures");
//{}...
